Having watched the bears a few times in the day I took the opportunity to ask one of the keepers if there was a particular time they tend to take a dip in the pool. Unfortunately I was advised there was no obvious pattern and it was just as and when.

I think the bear heard me, as she looked up from foraging in the long grass and made a b-line for the pool it was like she heard me, and proceeded to relax and wash all of the curry powder off herself from earlier in the day.

